    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Magazine Group Names an Officer</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Constance L. Hays</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Hays, Constance L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Magazine Publishers names Ellen W Oppenheim executive vice president and chief marketing officer, succeeding Christine Miller, who resigned in July (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Magazine Publishers of America in New York has named Ellen W. Oppenheim executive vice president and chief marketing officer. Ms. Oppenheim, 47, who joins the association in January, had been senior vice president and media director at the New York office of FCB Worldwide, part of True North Communications.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Magazine Publishers of America in New York has named Ellen W. Oppenheim executive vice president and chief marketing officer. Ms. Oppenheim, 47, who joins the association in January, had been senior vice president and media director at the New York office of FCB Worldwide, part of True North Communications.</p>
        <p>Ms. Oppenheim will succeed Christine Miller, who left the association in July to take the new post of executive vice president and chief marketing officer at Discovery.com cqin Bethesda, Md., part of Discovery Communications.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
